	<!-- Adrian -->
	<ThingDef ParentName="GreatWarHelmetBaseAdrian">
		<defName>GWH_M15_Adrian</defName>
		<label>Adrian M15</label>
		<description>The french adrian helmet was the first proper helmet introduced in the great war. Made of 0.7mm thick mild steel it stops most shrapnel from being lethal, but not bullets. The design is simmilar to firefighter helmets of that time. The insignia at the front of this helmet is fictional. There were many variations of these during the war including multiple stamped for cavelary, artillery and so on as well as countries. The Italian Adrian had painted insignia. Colors varied much as well. French Adrians were grey-blue or grey, khaki for colonial troops or the italian green ones. It was the most widespread helmet of the war even considered by the austro-hungarians as their main helmet as they had captured so many italian ones.</description>
			
		<graphicData>
			<texPath>GreatWarHelmets/Adrian/Helm</texPath>
		</graphicData>
		<apparel>
			<wornGraphicPath>GreatWarHelmets/Adrian/Helm</wornGraphicPath>
		</apparel>
	</ThingDef>
	<!-- Adrian_Browplate -->
	<ThingDef ParentName="GreatWarHelmetBaseAdrian">
		<defName>GWH_Adrian_Browplate</defName>
		<label>Adrian Browplate</label>
		<description>The Adrian Browplate weight 2.46kg and was 4mm thick. Its attachment to the adrian made it prone to fall onto the wearers nose at slight movements. Produced during 1916 it wasn't well liked by the troops and thus quickly discontinued.</description>

		<graphicData>
			<texPath>GreatWarHelmets/Adrian_Browplate/Helm</texPath>
		</graphicData>
		<apparel>
			<wornGraphicPath>GreatWarHelmets/Adrian_Browplate/Helm</wornGraphicPath>
		</apparel>
		<statBases>
			<WorkToMake>5500</WorkToMake>
			<MaxHitPoints>120</MaxHitPoints>
			<Mass>3.11</Mass>
			<StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>0.65</StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>
			<EquipDelay>2.5</EquipDelay>
		</statBases>
		<equippedStatOffsets>
			<MoveSpeed>-0.1</MoveSpeed>
			<AimingDelayFactor>-0.25</AimingDelayFactor>
		</equippedStatOffsets>
		<costStuffCount>65</costStuffCount>
	</ThingDef>
	<!-- Adrian_Polack -->
	<ThingDef ParentName="GreatWarHelmetBaseAdrian">
		<defName>GWH_Adrian_Polack</defName>
		<label>Adrian Polack</label>
		<description>The polack visor was first tested in 1916. There were 4 versions. This version represents the third, a slide on attachment for the M15 Adrian. The fourth one is the most used, attached permanently to the helmet. They saw service primarily at the battle of Verdun.</description>

		<graphicData>
			<texPath>GreatWarHelmets/Adrian_Polack/Helm</texPath>
		</graphicData>
