	</ThingDef>
	<!-- Gaede -->
	<ThingDef ParentName="GreatWarHelmetBase">
		<defName>GWH_Gaede</defName>
		<label>Gaede</label>
		<description>A project by the "Armeeabteilung Gaede" to reduce deaths due to head injuries resulted in the field production of this helmet in limited numbers. The Browplate was 6mm thick and attached to a cloth cap or sometimes a striped Pickelhaube. This Helmet would not be seen by many in the war as only 1500 wer produced and only a third actually used. Still it marks an important point in the development of military helmets in this war.</description>

