	<!-- Pickelhaube -->
	<ThingDef ParentName="GreatWarHelmetBase">
		<defName>GWH_M1897_Pickelhaube</defName>
		<label>M1897 Lederhelm mit Spitze "Pickelhaube"</label>
		<description>The "Pickelhaube" or officially "Leatherhelmet with spike" had long tradition within many militaries. This is a german on like the ones at the start of the great war. The star insignia is fictional. The Model is the 1897 one with later models changing the golden-brass metal to plain grey-silver, adding a removable spike and increasingly less decorated hessan covers to aid in concealment. The spike is worn by infantry and intended to deflect sabre blows from cavalry. Other roles had different attachments like the artillery with a ball instead of the spike.</description>
		
